[[File:Crock attack.png|thumb|''A crocodile attack.''|335x335px]]
Crocodiles typically preferred to ambush their enemies, sneaking up on them and using their powerful jaws to drag people below the water. While some would try to dismember their prey once below the waters, often times crocodiles attempted to drag prey back to their lairs before feasting upon them.{{Cite dragon/116/By Tooth and Claw|63}}

They were also known to lash out with their long tails, using them to disrupt an opponent's balance.
